10 ff. Tartara: here the place of the dead simply, equivalent to HadeS, Orcus. So Verg. G. 1, 36, nam le nec sperant Tartara regem. —- Panthoiden: Euphorbus, who was killed by Menelaus (ll. 17, 1— 60). His shield was hung up in the temple of Hera at Argos. Now Pythagoras claimed that he was the reincarnated Trojan hero, and to prove his claim went to the temple and took down Euphorbus' shield, recognizing it as the one he had carried when formerly on earth.
